      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The evidence supports that the capital gains changes are structurally designed to benefit high-net-worth individuals, which aligns with the criticism of wealth funneling. Proponents of the investment argument often cite theoretical economic models, but real-world data from past tax cuts suggests these benefits frequently accrue disproportionately at the top. Therefore, while both points are argued, the structural reality of the tax changes leans toward exacerbating inequality unless strong offsetting measures are present.",
      "source": "target",
